        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-21 14:30:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nHello Rujun,\n\nSome comments on your contribution.\n\n1) v_brgemu_install.sh, line 221: \"doen\" should be changed to \"done\"\n\n2) base_vcpe_vbrgemu_rackspace.yaml: you create a new parameter, sdnc_ip, which is never passed to the v_brgemu VM. To do so, you should add the following line somewhere under # Create config files:\n\necho \"__sdnc_ip__\" > /opt/config/sdnc_ip.txt  (you can choose the filename that you like).\n\nAlso, it's not clear to me how this value is used in v_brgemu_install.sh. I see there is a parameter called sdnc_ip, which reads the content of /opt/config/ip.txt, that is a file that you create and contains a local IP in the 192.168.X.X address space.\n\nCould you please patch your contribution for points 1) and 2), and let me know about the usage of sdnc_ip in v_brgemu_install.sh?\n\nThanks for the help,\n\nMarco",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
